INSERT INTO `events` VALUES (1,1,'Software meets hardware : bling a bot not a DIV','software-meets-hardware-bling-a-bot-not-a-div','none@none.com','','In this session we will escape from our beloved browser and start moving things in the real world.','In this session we will escape from our beloved browser and start moving things in the real world. Use your hard earned Node skills to start planning your escape to the Internet of things. We\'ll start simple you\'ll be tasked to pimp a bot add some bling and beep. Then it\'s up to you and your team to complete a few challenges with your blinged up bot.','<p>In this session we will escape from our beloved browser and start moving things in the real world. Use your hard earned Node skills to start planning your escape to the Internet of things. We&#39;ll start simple you&#39;ll be tasked to pimp a bot add some bling and beep. Then it&#39;s up to you and your team to complete a few challenges with your blinged up bot.</p>','2014-08-25','18:30:00','00:00:00','Western Cape','Cape Town','Woodstock','4th Floor, Woodstock Industrial Centre, 66 Albert Road, Cape Town, za','18.445812','-33.926782',NULL,NULL,285,'2014-10-27 13:56:55',0,'2017-12-07 10:31:23'),(2,1,'Intro to PCI-DSS, its importance and how you can become compliant','intro-to-pci-dss-its-importance-and-how-you-can-become-compliant','none@none.com','','Peach Payments and Ian Petzer will be giving us a intro into integrating online Card Payments into your NodeJS app and discussin','Peach Payments and Ian Petzer will be giving us a intro into integrating online Card Payments into your NodeJS app and discussing what the current landscape for PCI compliance in South-Africa looks like.','<p>Peach Payments and Ian Petzer will be giving us a intro into integrating online Card Payments into your NodeJS app and discussing what the current landscape for PCI compliance in South-Africa looks like.</p>','2014-03-25','18:30:00','00:00:00','Western Cape','Cape Town','Woodstock','4th Floor, Woodstock Industrial Centre, 66 Albert Road, Cape Town, za','18.445812','-33.926782',NULL,NULL,292,'2014-10-27 13:56:55',0,'2017-12-07 10:32:04'),(3,1,'Scaleconf 2014 NodeJS Workshop','scaleconf-2014-nodejs-workshop','none@none.com','','Intro to Node.js - a workshop by NodeCPT in collaboration with ScaleConf 2014 (scaleconf.org).','Intro to Node.js - a workshop by NodeCPT in collaboration with ScaleConf 2014 (scaleconf.org).\n\nRudolf Meijering (qurio.co) and Barry Botha (io.co.za) will give a hands-on practical introduction to Node.js. You\'ll walk away with a deeper appreciation behind the hype around Node.js as well as having written some server-side javascript yourself.\n\nThe event is open to anyone, but you\'ll benefit the most if you come prepared with the following:\n - an eagerness to learn\n - a laptop with Node.js and the Git command line client installed','<p>Intro to Node.js - a workshop by NodeCPT in collaboration with ScaleConf 2014 (scaleconf.org).</p>\n\n<p>Rudolf Meijering (qurio.co) and Barry Botha (io.co.za) will give a hands-on practical introduction to Node.js. You&#39;ll walk away with a deeper appreciation behind the hype around Node.js as well as having written some server-side javascript yourself.</p>\n\n<p>The event is open to anyone, but you&#39;ll benefit the most if you come prepared with the following:\n - an eagerness to learn\n - a laptop with Node.js and the Git command line client installed</p>','2014-04-12','09:00:00','00:00:00','Western Cape','Cape Town','Woodstock','6 Beach Road, Cape Town, za','18.4097386','-33.8995804',NULL,NULL,262,'2014-10-27 13:56:55',0,'2017-12-07 10:29:24'),(4,1,'Building USSD & SMS Apps with Vumi and NodeJS','building-ussd-sms-apps-with-vumi-and-nodejs','none@none.com','','With Africa and our limited connectivity, more and more consumers are only reachable via their mobile phones - a majority of tho','With Africa and our limited connectivity, more and more consumers are only reachable via their mobile phones - a majority of those being feature phones. With this in mind, USSD and SMS are powerful channels to help ensure that everyone is able to use the great apps you create.','<p>With Africa and our limited connectivity, more and more consumers are only reachable via their mobile phones - a majority of those being feature phones. With this in mind, USSD and SMS are powerful channels to help ensure that everyone is able to use the great apps you create.</p>','2014-04-29','18:00:00','00:00:00','Western Cape','Cape Town','Woodstock','4th Floor, Woodstock Industrial Centre, 66 Albert Road, Cape Town, za','18.445812','-33.926782',NULL,NULL,705,'2014-10-27 13:56:55',0,'2017-12-11 21:35:10'),(5,1,'Using Docker.io to provision cloud based services','using-docker-io-to-provision-cloud-based-services','none@none.com','','Simon Bishop will be presenting a use-case for Docker.io - for some idea about what this is about go to https://www.docker.io','Simon Bishop will be presenting a use-case for Docker.io - for some idea about what this is about go to https://www.docker.io','<p>Simon Bishop will be presenting a use-case for Docker.io - for some idea about what this is about go to https://www.docker.io</p>','2014-05-27','18:30:00','00:00:00','Western Cape','Cape Town','Woodstock','Longkloof Studios, Darters Road, Gardens, Cape Town, za','18.41151','-33.9288',NULL,NULL,267,'2014-10-27 13:56:55',0,'2017-12-07 10:31:29'),(6,1,'NodeJS and the Google Cloud Platform','nodejs-and-the-google-cloud-platform','none@none.com','','Google Cloud Platform enables developers to build, test and deploy applications on Google’s highly-scalable and reliable infrast','Google Cloud Platform enables developers to build, test and deploy applications on Google’s highly-scalable and reliable infrastructure. Choose from computing, storage and application services for your web, mobile and backend solutions.','<p>Google Cloud Platform enables developers to build, test and deploy applications on Google’s highly-scalable and reliable infrastructure. Choose from computing, storage and application services for your web, mobile and backend solutions.</p>','2014-05-27','18:30:00','00:00:00','Western Cape','Cape Town','','60 Hout Street, Cape Town, za','18.4199708','-33.9213455',NULL,NULL,262,'2014-10-27 13:56:55',0,'2017-12-07 10:30:29'),(8,1,'Resolving your intimacy problems with NodeJS','resolving-your-intimacy-problems-with-nodejs','qawemlilo@gmail.com','','The NodeJS community in Cape Town is very active so we\'ve been delving deeper into more advance topics.','The NodeJS community in Cape Town is very active so we\'ve been delving deeper into more advance topics.\r\n\r\nIt\'s time to get back to basics for a bit. And give everyone interested a good intro to NodeJS.\r\n\r\nMake your way to the event if you want to learn:\r\n\r\n-> What NodeJS is\r\n-> What makes NodeJS fast\r\n-> How NodeJS works under the hood to see what types of apps would work well with the platform\r\n-> Demo of writing a basic tcp server socket\r\n-> Common libraries to get you started\r\n-> Demo of writing a quick app using a popular framework - express\r\n-> Q&A\r\n\r\nEveryone should be able to get something out of this be. Be it those who want to go over the foundational concepts or anyone totally new to NodeJS and just interested.','<p>The NodeJS community in Cape Town is very active so we&#39;ve been delving deeper into more advance topics.</p>\n\n<p>It&#39;s time to get back to basics for a bit. And give everyone interested a good intro to NodeJS.</p>\n\n<p>Make your way to the event if you want to learn:</p>\n\n<p>-&gt; What NodeJS is\n-&gt; What makes NodeJS fast\n-&gt; How NodeJS works under the hood to see what types of apps would work well with the platform\n-&gt; Demo of writing a basic tcp server socket\n-&gt; Common libraries to get you started\n-&gt; Demo of writing a quick app using a popular framework - express\n-&gt; Q&amp;A</p>\n\n<p>Everyone should be able to get something out of this be. Be it those who want to go over the foundational concepts or anyone totally new to NodeJS and just interested.</p>','2014-09-29','18:30:00','00:00:00','Western Cape','Cape Town','','Lower Church St, Woodstock, Cape Town, 7915, South Africa','-33.924273','18.44922829999996','https://maps.google.com/maps/place?q=Lower+Church+St,+Woodstock,+Cape+Town,+7915,+South+Africa&ftid=0x1dcc5d98493d1187:0xddcede322a2c8fd5','http://www.meetup.com/nodecpt/events/199313812/',301,'2014-11-11 06:41:49',1,'2017-12-07 10:31:03'),(9,1,'The State of Node.js in South Africa and the way forward','the-state-of-node-js-in-south-africa-and-the-way-forward','qawemlilo@gmail.com','','Qawelesizwe Mlilo is a passionate NodeJS dev that has been building tools for the community and wants to show off what he has of','Qawelesizwe Mlilo is a passionate NodeJS dev that has been building tools for the community and wants to show off what he has offer to the community at large. In this session we take a step back from the usual tech only view. And have a look at the ecosystem of NodeJS in S.A, how it\'s growing and who\'s using it.\r\n\r\nSome topics include:\r\n\r\n• Active communities \r\n\r\n• Companies using Node.js \r\n\r\n• Projects/products built with Node in SA \r\n\r\n• Node.js job market \r\n\r\n• Node.js developers\r\n\r\nAfter which we will focus on what Qawelesizwe believes is the path forward to keep the momentum growing.\r\n\r\n• Building communities \r\n\r\n• Co-ordination of communities \r\n\r\n• Teaching & Learning (or learning through teaching) \r\n\r\n• Node.js Market(jobs and developers)\r\n\r\nQawelesizwe has been building a social platform for NodeJS in South-Africa. He will be introducing and defining his goal with the platform. Getting some useful feedback and any help from interested community members.','<p>Qawelesizwe Mlilo is a passionate NodeJS dev that has been building tools for the community and wants to show off what he has offer to the community at large. In this session we take a step back from the usual tech only view. And have a look at the ecosystem of NodeJS in S.A, how it&#39;s growing and who&#39;s using it.</p>\n\n<p>Some topics include:</p>\n\n<p>• Active communities </p>\n\n<p>• Companies using Node.js </p>\n\n<p>• Projects/products built with Node in SA </p>\n\n<p>• Node.js job market </p>\n\n<p>• Node.js developers</p>\n\n<p>After which we will focus on what Qawelesizwe believes is the path forward to keep the momentum growing.</p>\n\n<p>• Building communities </p>\n\n<p>• Co-ordination of communities </p>\n\n<p>• Teaching &amp; Learning (or learning through teaching) </p>\n\n<p>• Node.js Market(jobs and developers)</p>\n\n<p>Qawelesizwe has been building a social platform for NodeJS in South-Africa. He will be introducing and defining his goal with the platform. Getting some useful feedback and any help from interested community members.</p>','2014-10-28','18:30:00','00:00:00','Western Cape','Cape Town','','Lower Church St, Woodstock, Cape Town, 7915, South Africa','-33.924273','18.44922829999996','https://maps.google.com/maps/place?q=Lower+Church+St,+Woodstock,+Cape+Town,+7915,+South+Africa&ftid=0x1dcc5d98493d1187:0xddcede322a2c8fd5','http://www.meetup.com/nodecpt/events/199314412/',407,'2014-11-11 06:47:00',1,'2017-12-07 10:31:59'),(10,1,'Cape Town International Nodebots Day','cape-town-international-nodebots-day','andre@gmail.com','','Join us on International Nodebots day and build a Javascript powered robot. ','Join us on International Nodebots day and build a Javascript powered robot. \r\n\r\nThis will be the first Nodebots day on African soil. \r\n\r\nWhat we doing\r\n\r\nWe will start the day of learning the basics of hacking hardware using Javascript, getting those LED\'s to blink and strobe. Once everyone feels in control of LED\'s we will control a few other pieces of hardware using Javascript.\r\n\r\nBy this time you will be so confident you will start building a robot! Meet Sumobot, we might even give him/her some eyes. Definitely hang around for the first Sumobot fight in Cape Town. Your own teams sumobot might be crowned the first ever Somubot champion of Africa.\r\n\r\nIf you have your own Arduino, RasPi or what not based bot you would like to hack in the company of others please also please join us. We are a curious lot!\r\n\r\nWhat to bring\r\n\r\n• A laptop if you have one\r\n\r\n• An Arduino starter kit of sorts:\r\n\r\n    • https://www.robotics.org.za/index.php?route=product/product&product_id=61&search=sparkfun\r\n\r\n    • http://netram.co.za/1068-arduino-proto-kit.html\r\n\r\n    • Other things you would like to hack\r\n\r\n• A AR.Drone 2.0. Parrot drone if you have one... we\'ll give it Javascript wings\r\n\r\n• Any PS3 dual shock or Wii controllers you have laying around...\r\n\r\n• Don\'t forget a sense of humor and some crazy ideas!\r\n\r\nWhat will you get?\r\n\r\n• The entry fee of R200, will give you access to parts for building a Sumobot:\r\n\r\n    • We will work in groups of 4 \r\n\r\n    •  If you would like to build one to take home, it can be arranged.\r\n\r\n    • For R575 you can buy an Arduino(DFRDuino) starter kit - with everything you need to learn the basics of using Javascript with hardware.\r\n\r\nWe will provide lunch.\r\n\r\nSponsors\r\n\r\nWe are currently looking for sponsors which will bring the cost of the day down. Shout if you know about prospective sponsors!\r\n\r\nThats about it.\r\n\r\nOld hands?\r\n\r\nAre you an old hand at Robotics, Arduino, Node or even Johhny-5 please contact me we need some hands on the day.','<p>Join us on International Nodebots day and build a Javascript powered robot. </p>\n\n<p>This will be the first Nodebots day on African soil. </p>\n\n<p>What we doing</p>\n\n<p>We will start the day of learning the basics of hacking hardware using Javascript, getting those LED&#39;s to blink and strobe. Once everyone feels in control of LED&#39;s we will control a few other pieces of hardware using Javascript.</p>\n\n<p>By this time you will be so confident you will start building a robot! Meet Sumobot, we might even give him/her some eyes. Definitely hang around for the first Sumobot fight in Cape Town. Your own teams sumobot might be crowned the first ever Somubot champion of Africa.</p>\n\n<p>If you have your own Arduino, RasPi or what not based bot you would like to hack in the company of others please also please join us. We are a curious lot!</p>\n\n<p>What to bring</p>\n\n<p>• A laptop if you have one</p>\n\n<p>• An Arduino starter kit of sorts:</p>\n\n<pre><code>• https://www.robotics.org.za/index.php?route=product/product&amp;product_id=61&amp;search=sparkfun\n\n• http://netram.co.za/1068-arduino-proto-kit.html\n\n• Other things you would like to hack</code></pre>\n\n<p>• A AR.Drone 2.0. Parrot drone if you have one... we&#39;ll give it Javascript wings</p>\n\n<p>• Any PS3 dual shock or Wii controllers you have laying around...</p>\n\n<p>• Don&#39;t forget a sense of humor and some crazy ideas!</p>\n\n<p>What will you get?</p>\n\n<p>• The entry fee of R200, will give you access to parts for building a Sumobot:</p>\n\n<pre><code>• We will work in groups of 4 \n\n•  If you would like to build one to take home, it can be arranged.\n\n• For R575 you can buy an Arduino(DFRDuino) starter kit - with everything you need to learn the basics of using Javascript with hardware.</code></pre>\n\n<p>We will provide lunch.</p>\n\n<p>Sponsors</p>\n\n<p>We are currently looking for sponsors which will bring the cost of the day down. Shout if you know about prospective sponsors!</p>\n\n<p>Thats about it.</p>\n\n<p>Old hands?</p>\n\n<p>Are you an old hand at Robotics, Arduino, Node or even Johhny-5 please contact me we need some hands on the day.</p>','2014-07-26','10:00:00','00:00:00','Western Cape','Cape Town','','66 Albert Rd, Woodstock, Cape Town, 7915, South Africa','-33.9269','18.445820000000026','https://maps.google.com/maps/place?q=66+Albert+Rd,+Woodstoc