 of these</p>\n\n<p>• An Nodebot starter kit with an ultrasonic sensor and bluetooth support - a robot chassis/car to built on the day and to take home. With or without an Arduino. Price to be confirmed.</p>\n\n<p>• Sensors - ultrasonic, Infrared PIR - R65</p>\n\n<p>• Bluetooth serial module: R135</p>\n\n<p>• Ask if you need something else</p>\n\n<p>Dedicated parking will be available.</p>','2014-09-20','09:30:00','00:00:00','Western Cape','Cape Town','','66 Albert Rd, Woodstock, Cape Town, 7915, South Africa','-33.9269','18.445820000000026','https://maps.google.com/maps/place?q=66+Albert+Rd,+Woodstock,+Cape+Town,+7915,+South+Africa&ftid=0x1dcc5d995de78a9f:0x5f1adf5bd13ed86f','http://www.meetup.com/Cape-Town-Nodebots/events/202044572/',282,'2014-11-11 06:56:24',1,'2017-12-10 06:17:25'),(12,1,'A Dash Of Robotics','a-dash-of-robotics','qawemlilo@gmail.com','','It\'s time we started to do regular, shorter meet-ups. We\'ll begin by talking about some of the things we\'ve been building, and t','\r\n\r\nIt\'s time we started to do regular, shorter meet-ups. We\'ll begin by talking about some of the things we\'ve been building, and the technologies we\'re been using to build them.\r\n\r\nJoin us for interesting discussions about robots, code and robots, robots and robots, and robots. Bring your laptops, for programming the robots. Seriously. Bring your laptops.\r\n','<p>It&#39;s time we started to do regular, shorter meet-ups. We&#39;ll begin by talking about some of the things we&#39;ve been building, and the technologies we&#39;re been using to build them.</p>\n\n<p>Join us for interesting discussions about robots, code and robots, robots and robots, and robots. Bring your laptops, for programming the robots. Seriously. Bring your laptops.</p>','2014-11-18','18:30:00','00:00:00','Western Cape','Cape Town','','Lower Church St, Woodstock, Cape Town, 7915, South Africa','-33.924273','18.44922829999996','https://maps.google.com/maps/place?q=Lower+Church+St,+Woodstock,+Cape+T